        "created_at": "2018-09-27T22:29:02.175Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"cespare\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"736\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/cespare/48/36_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> cespare:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>How do I delete and recreate the DB? I don\u2019t care about any of the data; I\u2019m just trying to experiment with stuff quickly. It\u2019s not clear from any of the admin or configuration documentation that I\u2019ve read.</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>The steps you took are an effective way to do this, particularly when everything is on one machine.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"cespare\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"736\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/cespare/48/36_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> cespare:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>What would the correct procedure have been for adjusting the number of storage workers in a safe way?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>See <a href=\"https://apple.github.io/foundationdb/administration.html#removing-machines-from-a-cluster\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Administration \u2014 FoundationDB 7.1</a> for a description of this procedure.</p>\n<p>EDIT: I should add that the procedure above is for removing machines, but the steps are roughly the same. In place of disabling the service, you would disable the specific processes (e.g. by modifying foundationdb.conf).</p>",
